-- South African Corn Drops Following Decline in Prices in Chicago
-- B y   A m o g e l a n g   M b a t h a
-- 2013-06-28T14:28:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-28/south-african-corn-drops-following-decline-in-prices-in-chicago.html
South African corn futures slumped
following a drop in the U.S.  Yellow corn for delivery in September settled 1.3 percent
lower at 2,258 rand ($233.89) a metric ton on the South African
Futures Exchange in Johannesburg. The white variety fell 0.9
percent to 2,337.40 rand a ton. Prices in  Chicago  declined 1.1
percent. The U.S. Department of Agriculture reports on U.S.
acreage planted and stockpiles at noon in  Washington .  Wheat for delivery in December fell 1.3 percent to 3,377
rand a ton.  South Africa is the continentâ€™s largest producer of corn.
Meal from white corn is a staple food while the yellow kind is
mainly used as animal feed in South Africa.  To contact the reporter on this story:
